From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Verrilli <msv@pobox.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 04:16:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ml/backend/ggml: port TurboQuant kernels to Metal

Mirrors the CUDA TurboQuant ops on Apple Silicon. Adds Metal kernels for
encode (with optional asymmetric per-sub-block mean and 32-channel
outlier split), dequant, and fused flash attention. Covers head dims 64,
128, and 256.

The Metal kernels share the on-disk block format with CUDA so blocks
written by one backend decode under the other unchanged.
---
